    "The z-hypercharges are required to satisfy a set of six anomaly cancellation equations (ACE) [34], suitably written definingz q = 3 i=1 z q i L, z u = 3 i=1 z u i R, z d = 3 i=1 z d i R,(4)z ℓ = 3 i=1 z ℓ i L, z ν = 3 i=1 z ν i R, z e = 3 i=1 z e i R,(5)and z(2)f = i=1,2,3 z 2 f i, z(3)f = i=1,2,3 z 3 f i.",
    "(6)f i are the fermionsf i = q i L, u i R, d i R, ℓ i L, e i R, ν i R for the generations i = 1, 2, 3.In a notation where groups indicate the gauge bosons in triangular graphs, the anomaly cancellation equations read:1.",
    "[SU (3) C] 2 U(1) ′: A 33z = 2z q -z u -z d = 0; (7) 2.",
    "[SU (2)] 2 U(1) ′: A 22z = 3z q + z l = 0; (8) 3.",
